Feedback:
The executed tests indicate ANOMALOUS behavior suggestive of 'SwitchInternalFault'. When the switch was set to the closed position (or was already closed), the measured resistance between the switch’s terminals was extremely high (open circuit, ~998 MΩ), indicating no continuity. This is not expected—when closed, the switch should show very low resistance (continuity).

The switch continued to read as an open circuit even after being intentionally set to the open position, which matches expectations for the open state, but the failure to achieve continuity in the closed state is conclusive evidence of an internal fault within the switch mechanism or contacts.

Recommended action: Replace or repair the switch, as it is not functioning properly.
